{"lemma":"سَوِيقِ","slug":"سَوِيقِ","root":"س.#.ق","root_slug":"س-_-ق","root_link":"/words/roots/س-_-ق","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n21295"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B3%D9%8E%D9%88%D9%90%D9%8A%D9%82%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"peduncle, stipe, stalk etc."},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"gruel of barley (most often) with dates, tisane (and we refer to the web for detailled recipes)","examples":[{"text":"غسل الزيت\nيؤخذ من الزيت أصفاه مقدار ما يراد فيجعل في طنجير ويصب عليه قليل ماء قراح وتلقى فيه تمرتان ومقدار كف سويق مصرور في خرقة كتان ويغلى غليانا رفيقا بنار لينة حتى يذهب الماء ويبقى الزيت صافيا ثم يخرج عنه السويق والتمر ويبرد الزيت ويستعمل عند الحاجة","english":"How to wash olive oil.\nTake as much as you like from the purest olive oil, cast it in a cauldron, pour on it a bit of limpid water, throw into it two dates and a handful of flour (translates Kahl) tied up in a cloth of linen, and boil (all this) gently on a low flame until the water vanishes and the oil remains in a clear state; take out the flour and the dates, let the oil cool off, and use it as required."}]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Diminutive of سَاق (sāq, “leg”).\n\nPassive participle form from some meaning of سَاقَ (sāqa)."},"ipa":["/su.wajq/","/sa.wiːq/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n21295","headword_ar":"سَوِيقٌ","root":"swq","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Meal of parched barley"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aEiyr","text_ar":"شَعِير"},{"kind":"text","text":"), or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the species thereof,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"similar grain, called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sulot","text_ar":"سُلْت"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"likewise parched;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and it is also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of wheat;"},{"kind":"text","text":"but is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mostly made of barley"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$Eyr","text_ar":"شعير"},{"kind":"text","text":"); (MF, TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what is made of wheat"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of barley;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"well known:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K, TA:) [it is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"generally made into a kind of gruel,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thick ptisan, being moistened with water,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"clarified butter,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fat of a sheep's tail, &c.;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lat~a","text_ar":"لَتَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":";) and is therefore said (in the Msb in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hsw","text_ar":"حسو"},{"kind":"text","text":"and in the KT voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^akolN","text_ar":"اَكْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", &c.,) to be supped, or sipped, not eaten: but it is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"likewise thus called when dry;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and in this state is taken in the palm of the hand and conveyed to the mouth, or licked up: (see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAf~q","text_ar":"حَافّق"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qamiHa","text_ar":"قَمِحَ"},{"kind":"text","text":":) it is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"also made of other grains beside those mentioned above;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of several mealy fruits; of the fruit of the Theban palm;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HatiY~N","text_ar":"حَتِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":";) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the carob;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xar~uwbN","text_ar":"خَرُّوبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":";)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"&c.:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] it is also, sometimes, with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"S","text_ar":"ص"},{"kind":"text","text":": so says IDrd in the Jm: and he adds, I think it to be of the dial. of Benoo-Temeem: it is peculiar to that of Benul-' Ambar: (O, TA:) the n. un. [meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a portion,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mess, thereof"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":": (AAF, TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"j$","text_ar":"جش"},{"kind":"text","text":":) and the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asowiqapN","text_ar":"اَسْوِقَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Wine:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AA, K:) also called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sawiyqu Alkaromi","text_ar":"سَوِيقُ الكَرْمِ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (AA, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","Msb","K","TA","O","AA"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}